ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would definitely recommend this course to another student. I think it got better the whole semester, and I'm sure it would only be better if it should be offered again.See above.
I would definitely recommend this class to everyone who is interested in music.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This opened a world of music completely unknown to me. That alone would make it worthwhile. Moreover, as a musician/music-scholar, I think it's only responsible that I learn about this stuff. Lastly, it acts as a perfect window into the history of 20th c. music, music historiography, the production of new music, the relationship between music and other arts... Do I really need to go on?
This class was mind-opening and gave me so many ideas about what I might do in my future research. A great class.
